Title: احتجاج
Description (English): A black-and-white poster showing a painting of a weeping woman carrying her killed child in her arms

AltTitle.other: A Figure of a Palestinian Fighter

Title: الجحيم للقتلة
Description (English): A black-and-white poster showing a painting of a weeping woman as she carries her killed child with her hand

Title: جرائم بشعة
Description (English): A black-and-white poster showing a painting of a wounded man carrying another wounded man; and his amputated parts

Title: طفل وقنابل
Description (English): A black-and-white poster showing a painting of a child in pain as bombs fall down on him

Title: "ولنا لقاء"، لوحة للفنان كتسيكويانيس، 1989
AltTitle.other: 'This is not Our Last Word', a Painting by Katsikogiannis, 1989
Description (English): A poster features an artwork titled 'This is not our Last Word' by Greek artist Katsikogiannis. The art print depicts a Palestinian woman with a bandolier slung over her shoulder carries her massacred children and walks shoulder to shoulder with a Palestinian man with a gun. Crowds of Palestinian fidayeen appear on the horizon.

Title: الويل للقتلة
Description (English): A black-and-white poster showing a painting of a weeping woman as she carries her killed child with her hand

Title: المجرم الدموي
Description (English): A black-and-white poster showing a painting of an armed wolf; with a rifle on his shoulder, a missile in his hand, and a military helmet over his head. (This painting portrays Israel as a predator)

Title: الغلاف مهدى من الفنان اليوناني كتسيكويانس إلى الشعب الفلسطيني المناضل
AltTitle.other: Contribution Of The Greek Sculptor-painter Katsicoyanni To The Palestinian People
Description (English): A colour poster showing the cover of one of the Greek artist; Katsicoyanni, paintings

Title: ملصق لمعرض نُصب تذكارية مقارنة، لتوم نِكلسون، 2012
AltTitle.other: A Proposition for a Monument, Comparative Monument (Palestine), Tom Nicholson, 2012
Description (English): Proposition for a monument, articulated as two-sided off-set printed poster, each 50 × 50 cm, for visitors to take away, and also pasted up around Ramallah, this colour poster shows a monument commemorating the presence of Australian soldiers in Palestine during World War I and their role in the 1917 British capture of Beʾr as-Sabeʿ.
Related Sub-Collection: Ali Kazak Sub-collection 6: The Posters of "Comparative Monument (Palestine)" Exhibition

AltTitle.other: A Proposition for a Monument, Comparative Monument (Palestine), Tom Nicholson, 2012
